headline: Wells Fargo Bank Decreases Prime Rate to 7.25 Percent
summary: SAN FRANCISCO, September 17, 2025--Wells Fargo Bank, N.A., said today it is decreasing its prime rate to 7.25 percent from 7.50 percent, effective tomorrow, Sept. 18, 2025.

headline: These Big Bank Stocks Are Breakout Ready Ahead Of Fed
summary: Many major bank stocks trade near record highs and in some cases near buy points, as the Fed ponders an interest-rate cut likely to influence rate-sensitive financials.  The Federal Reserve will decide today whether to resume cutting interest rates.  The Fed started loosening monetary policy a year ago, but so far hasn't changed the target Fed funds rate at all this year.
